TITLE: GraphQL Mutation for Multiple File Upload with Payload
DESCRIPTION: Defines a GraphQL mutation `multipleUploadWithPayload` that accepts a list of `UploadFile!` input objects. This allows uploading multiple files, each associated with its own set of data (like an ID), within a single mutation. It returns details for each processed item in the list.
SOURCE: https://github.com/99designs/gqlgen/blob/master/_examples/fileupload/readme.md#_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: GraphQL
CODE:
```
{
  query: `
    mutation($req: [UploadFile!]!)
      multipleUploadWithPayload(req: $req) {
        id,
        name,
        content
      }
    }
  `,
  variables: {
    req: [
        {
            id: 1,
            File, // b.txt
        },
        {
            id: 2,
            File, // c.txt
        }
    ] 
  }
}
```

