TITLE: Custom Todo Model with Lazy-Loaded User Field - Go
DESCRIPTION: Defines a custom Todo struct to support more efficient data fetching. The struct includes a UserID and a pointer to a User object, with JSON struct tags for serialization. This supports separation of concerns, enabling user details to be fetched only when requested.
SOURCE: https://github.com/99designs/gqlgen/blob/master/docs/content/getting-started.md#_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
package model

type Todo struct {
	ID     string `json:"id"`
	Text   string `json:"text"`
	Done   bool   `json:"done"`
	UserID string `json:"userId"`
	User   *User  `json:"user"`
}
```

