TITLE: Testing SSE Subscription with Curl in Bash
DESCRIPTION: This Bash command uses `curl` to test a GraphQL subscription over Server-Sent Events (SSE). It sends a POST request to the `/query` endpoint with the subscription query in the body, and includes the necessary headers `accept: text/event-stream` and `content-type: application/json` to indicate an SSE request. The `-N` flag prevents buffering, showing events as they arrive.
SOURCE: https://github.com/99designs/gqlgen/blob/master/docs/content/recipes/subscriptions.md#_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
curl -N --request POST --url http://localhost:8080/query \
--data '{"query":"subscription { currentTime { unixTime timeStamp } }"}' \
-H "accept: text/event-stream" -H 'content-type: application/json' \
--verbose
```

