TITLE: Initializing gqlgen Plugin Entrypoint in Go
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines a standalone Go main package to set up gqlgen code generation using a custom plugin. It loads gqlgen configuration from default locations, and then calls api.Generate applying the custom plugin via api.AddPlugin(yourplugin.New()). An error during config loading or code generation exits the program with a non-zero status. Dependencies include gqlgen's api, config, and plugin packages. This file is intended to be run via go generate as an alternative to the default gqlgen generate command, enabling the injection of custom plugins.
