TITLE: Defining GraphQL Type with Nullable and Non-Nullable Fields
DESCRIPTION: This GraphQL schema snippet defines a type `OmitEmptyJsonTagTest` with one non-nullable field (`ValueNonNil: String!`) and one nullable field (`Value: String`). This difference influences the JSON serialization behavior of generated Go models.
SOURCE: https://github.com/99designs/gqlgen/blob/master/docs/content/reference/model-generation.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: graphql
CODE:
```
type OmitEmptyJsonTagTest {
    ValueNonNil: String!
    Value: String
}
```

